{"title": "On Holy Images", "description": "\u201cA Treatise on Images will not be out of place in a public which is confusing the making of images with the making of idols. A great Christian of the eighth century found himself called upon to face an imperial Iconoclast, Leo the Isaurian, who waged war against holy images, on the plausible pretext that they withdrew honour from God. He would willingly have remained silent, but he would not bury his talent of eloquence. He brought it forth and witnessed to the teaching of the Church...\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe seventh General Council condemned Leo\u2019s assault. And the special champion of holy Images is St John Damascene, whose treatise is now published for the first time in English.\u201d (Summary adapted by The Reader from the Translator's Preface)", "duration": 12072, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "6022", "name": "Saint John of Damascus"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/onholyimages_2512_librivox/on_holy_imsges_2512.jpg", "copyright_year": "1898", "genres": ["Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Magdalene Miller"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Part 1", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onholyimages_2512_librivox/onholyimages_01_damascene_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1300}, {"section": 2, "title": "Part 1 continued", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onholyimages_2512_librivox/onholyimages_02_damascene_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1368}, {"section": 3, "title": "Part 1 continued", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onholyimages_2512_librivox/onholyimages_03_damascene_64kb.mp3", "duration": 987}, {"section": 4, "title": "Part 1 continued", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onholyimages_2512_